NY Times Best sellers Web data connector - Steps
Step 1: Download the Web data connector
Navigate to
https://tableau.github.io/webdataconnector/
 Read documentation
 Check the API reference
 Click on Get started to go through the
details
 Download the API libraries
Step 2: Verify the download folder structure
Navigate to the folder wherever you have copied
the web data connector files.
 Verify that there is an example sub folder
 Inside example you should have JS and
HTML sub folders.
 Inside HTML sub-folder, Clone
earthquakeUSGS.html and create a new
file for your API entry point (i.e HTML
page)
 Inside JS sub-folder, Clone
earthquakeUSGS.js and create a new file
for the API logic (i.e calling REST and
parsing JSON response)
Step 3: Verify the Book.html and Book.js – Copy
Download the HTML and JS for
Books
 Navigate to
https://github.com/muthukumarsm/NYTimes_Bestsellers
 Download the following files
 Books.html
 Books.js
 Book Details.html
 Book Details.js
Step 4: File deployment
Deploy the files in webserver
 Deploy html and JS files in the webserver
 Ensure you can access the HTML and JS
files from Simulator.html present under
the webdataconnector
 Once simulator access is successful,
Launch the HTML (books.html and book
details.html) from Tableau Desktop -
Web data connector connection and
download the API data.
